First Lady Melania Trump addressed the spouses of the National Governors Association at the White House, expressing her condolences for the recent shooting in Florida and calling for action to help prevent such tragedies. She emphasized the importance of adults taking responsibility in helping children manage issues such as social media habits, drug abuse, and addiction. Melania urged the audience to promote values such as encouragement, kindness, compassion, and respect in children, and asked for their support in her efforts to protect and nurture the well-being of children across the country.